<TITLE> Court security upped over Khaleda appearance </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 7 (bdnews24.com)--The government has heightened security measures at the Dhaka Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court premises ahead of the appearance of opposition BNP chief Khaleda Zia in the Zia Orphanage Trust case on Monday. Senior officials of Dhaka Metropolitan Police were on guard around the court. Public prosecutor Mosharraf Hossain Kajal was also suggesting police officials measures. Khaleda's counsel Sanaullah Miah said his client was scheduled to appear in the court at around 1pm. The hearing of the acceptance of the charges of Zia Orphanage Trust case will be held in the court of senior metropolitan special judge A N M Bashirullah. The Anticorruption Commission pressed charges in the court against Khaleda, elder son Tarique Rahman and four others on Aug 5. The hearing was deferred twice on Aug 12 and 30 since Khaleda did not appear in the court on security reasons. The ACC filed the case with Ramna Police Station on July 3, 2008 on charges of embezzling Tk 2.10 crore of Zia Orphanage Trust, which allegedly existed only on papers . b
